    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-01T12:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-01T12:29:00-05:00" n="266"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/750</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-01T21:00:00+03:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 4, 2.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2050. <persName corresp="#p_JBGWV1">Judson</persName> saw <persName
                        corresp="#p_TLDB1">Trotsky</persName> to-day with my approval as at
                    yesterday’s meeting of Allied chiefs I advocated unofficial effort to influence
                    armistice terms at conference beginning to-morrow. No objection was offered to
                    each chief’s exerting such influence unofficially and not personally. <persName
                        corresp="#p_JBGWV1">Judson</persName> making full report to War
                        Department.<note n="1" xml:id="d266fn1">See <hi rend="italic"
                        >infra</hi>.</note> Says no friction attended first session and thinks some
                    good accomplished. My desire was as indicated my 2039, November 28, 12
                        noon,<note n="2" xml:id="d266fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_252">p. 252</ref>.</note> to
                    throw safeguards around separate armistice, if inevitable, that would protect
                    other fronts and prevent transfer thereto of German troops now confronting
                    Russian Army; also to prevent liberation of Austrian-German prisoners and
                    Russian prisoners. <persName corresp="#p_TLDB1">Trotsky</persName> told
                        <persName corresp="#p_JBGWV1">Judson</persName> had thought of such
                    provisos.</p>
                <p>Allied chiefs still carefully avoiding recognition. Reports continue that
                    Bolsheviki will not have majority in Assembly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
